title: Conquering Florida: Jet Skiing in Key West
text:
Updated: 2:50 p.m. Wednesday, Aug. 26, 2015 | Posted: 10:38 a.m. Wednesday, Aug. 26, 2015 Conquering Florida: Jet Skiing in Key West In Partnership with VisitFlorida.com 
Known for his greatness in motocross, Florida native Ricky Carmichael retires his bike for the day to conquer Florida by jet skiing completely around the island of Key West. In this episode of Conquering Florida, Ricky Carmichael and his manager, J.H. Leale, take a 28-mile adventure around Key West, Florida, which takes them from the Gulf of Mexico to the Atlantic Ocean and back again. All along the way, they encounter some truly unique and amazing aquatic sites and sounds that can only be experienced off the coasts of Florida. The team at Sunset Watersports were great guides for this trip and helped keep Ricky and J.H. safe no matter how wet and wild they got.
